ear to be missing. Could you please provide the following additional inform=
ation and records: Correspondence



Kia ora, Zach and the Privacy Team,

Thank you for sharing the material to date. I=E2=80=99ve reviewed the docum=
ents and can see that several items appear to be missing. Could you please =
provide the following additional information and records:

Correspondence and communications
(Note: The timestamps referenced below appear to follow a non-NZT time zone=
 (likely UTC). Please adjust your searches accordingly.)


     *   The email from Stephen Walker (ASUR NZ Consultant) to Grant Metson=
, referred to in the email sent by Grant Metson  to himself dated 12 August=
 2025 at 04:59.
     *   The correspondence referred to in the email between Lei Yu and Gra=
nt on or around Sunday, 17 August 2025, as mentioned again in the email of =
Monday, 18 August 2025 at 20:59.
     *   Any phone conversations between Grant Metson and Lei Yu (ASUR NZ, =
Building Consultant, +64 21 467 094) on or around Sunday, 17 August 2025.
     *   Any calls between Grant Metson and Lei Yu (ASUR NZ) on or after Th=
ursday, 21 August 2025.
     *   As referenced in the email from Grant to Stephen Walker dated 16 S=
eptember 2025 at 3:07 am, details or recordings of the call between Grant a=
nd Stephen that occurred earlier that day or the day prior.

Internal and external communications referencing my claim


     *   Any emails, chats, text, transcripts or notes in your systems that=
 contain C90306048.
     *   Any emails, chats, text,  transcripts or notes in your systems tha=
t contain =E2=80=9C23 Mays=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9C23 Mays Road=E2=80=9D.
     *   Any emails, texts, or chat messages to or from the following addre=
sses or individuals that reference claim C90306048, my propert (=E2=80=9C23=
 Mays=E2=80=9D)  or myself (under any name variation, as I see often misspe=
lled):

        *   Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz<mailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>
        *   Bryan.Strong@tower.co.nz<mailto:Bryan.Strong@tower.co.nz>
        *   Megan.Jensen@tower.co.nz<mailto:Megan.Jensen@tower.co.nz>
        *   Kelly.Mason@tower.co.nz<mailto:Kelly.Mason@tower.co.nz>
        *   Chris.Cornwall@tower.co.nz<mailto:Chris.Cornwall@tower.co.nz>
        *   Zach.Pion@tower.co.nz<mailto:Zach.Pion@tower.co.nz>
        *   Sasha.Cotterill@tower.co.nz<mailto:Sasha.Cotterill@tower.co.nz>
        *   and any other person copied or involved in communications relat=
ed to the claim.

     *   Any internal emails or external communications (including subject =
lines, message text, or attachment names) that include the text =E2=80=9CC9=
0306048=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9C23 Mays Road=E2=80=9D / =E2=80=9C23 Mays=E2=80=
=9D.
     *   Any internal communications (texts, chats, or call notes) concerni=
ng the claim, the property, or myself.
     *   Any phone transcripts that include =E2=80=9CC90306048=E2=80=9D, =
=E2=80=9C23 Mays Road=E2=80=9D, or =E2=80=9C23 Mays=E2=80=9D.


Notification of privacy breach

I would also like to formally notify a potential privacy breach.
On 10 August 2025, Grant Metson shared my name and mobile number with Steph=
en Walker (ASUR NZ) by email without my consent and without a clear busines=
s reason. Given that I have since raised concerns about Mr Walker=E2=80=99s=
 independence, I believe this disclosure was inappropriate and may present =
a risk to my privacy and safety.

Please confirm that this incident will be logged and investigated in accord=
ance with Tower=E2=80=99s privacy obligations and the Privacy Act 2020.

Please confirm receipt of this email and advise when I can expect a respons=
e or update on both the information request and the privacy breach notifica=
tion.

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella


